description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a newly qualified, or soon to be, &lt;strong&gt;Registered Mental Health Nurse (RMN) &lt;/strong&gt;with a passion for delivering outstanding care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working 42 hours per week at Cygnet Sherwood House. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Sherwood House&lt;/strong&gt; is a 30 bed specialist high dependency inpatient rehabilitation service for men dedicated to providing a high quality environment for promoting long-term recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to enjoy excellent career prospects while reaping the rewards of making a difference to others – every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your programme includes…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support from Cygnet’s Preceptorship Development Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum two shifts per week working with your nominated preceptor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preceptee supernumery 1st week on ward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly CPD Days off the ward (specialist and general)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical supervision, minimum 1 session per month&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managerial supervision, minimum 1 session per month&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preceptee Group Meetings on site and across the Cygnet group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certificate and letter of completion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent training opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An action plan will then be created by you and your preceptor for the following six months to enhance identified strengths and address areas of development, taking you to your first annual appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day-to-Day…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer prescribed medicines with Healthcare procedure and Healthcare Commission guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the management team to develop the service, including clinical direction meetings, training , case study reviews  audit, and improve quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce outstanding written reports based on your nursing assessments and observations and deliver them at CTRM meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend all training and engage in CPD to further knowledge and promote nursing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Under NMC guidelines, ensure that individual care plans are complete &amp; maintained collectively with residents, relatives and other healthcare professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS and employee discount scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% NMC registration renewal paid by Cygnet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCNi membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bespoke career pathways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company paid Life Assurance scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plus many more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A newly qualified, or soon to be, RMN – you’ll have…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to maintain documentation, undertake audits and demonstrate integrity in your role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A good understanding of the Mental Health Act 1983 and latest nursing practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to patient recovery in order to effectively monitor, manage and reduce risk Compassion, resilience and a dedication to empower and support service user independence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in leadership, research and assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge on behavioural interventions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Health Care &lt;/strong&gt;has been providing a national network of high quality specialist mental health services for more than 30 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe that our programme of individual care and attention for our service users will contribute to their well-being and comfort, so that they will be able to go on to live in the wider community with appropriate support, guidance and assistance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dedicated clinical teams provide a multi-disciplinary input including occupational therapy, psychology, psychiatry and vocational training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a Preceptorship / newly qualified Nurse (Mental Health) that is ready to make a positive change?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CQC overall rating &quot;&lt;strong&gt;Outstanding&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please click on the ‘apply now’ link below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join us!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
